<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="10" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,573,2005]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[151,209,573,598]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male</emphasis>
. Black. Scutellum with two yellow spots on each lateral margin and a spot at apex. Forewing with fine yellowish-brown spots. 
<emphasis box="[428,512,609,634]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Female</emphasis>
. Head black, pronotum black variably marked with yellowish-brown on posterior margin. Scutellum bright yellow with basal angles black. Forewing spots more pronounced than in male and sometimes coalescing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,573,2005]" box="[199,600,717,742]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
Vertex relatively long (
<figureCitation box="[456,587,717,742]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–13" captionStart-1="FIGURES 14–26" captionStartId-0="19.[151,264,1943,1966]" captionStartId-1="20.[151,264,1851,1874]" captionTargetBox-0="[180,1406,215,1888]" captionTargetBox-1="[195,1406,213,1815]" captionTargetId-0="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1922]" captionTargetId-1="figure@20.[151,1436,193,1830]" captionTargetPageId-0="19" captionTargetPageId-1="20" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–13. Habitus of species of Penthimia. 1–4. P. attenuata Distant: 1–2. Male, dorsal and lateral view; 3–4. Color variation in female. 5–9. P. compacta Walker, 5–6. Male, dorsal and lateral view; 7–9, colour variation in female. 10–11. P. curvata sp. nov., holotype male, dorsal and lateral view. 12–13. P.ereba, male, dorsal and ventral view." captionText-1="FIGURES 14–26. Habitus of species of Penthimia. 14–17.P.ereba, colour variation in female; 18. P. fraterna Distant, female topotype, dorsal view; 19–20. Female P. funebris Distant, dorsal and lateral view. 21–22. Female P. maculosa Distant, dorsal and lateral view; 23–24. Holotype male P. meghalayensis, dorsal and lateral view. 25–26. Female P. mudononensis Distant, dorsal and lateral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/1135480/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/1135482/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Figs 12–17</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,573,2005]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[199,371,753,778]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer with rounded caudal margin, ventrocaudal area with long stout setae. Subgenital plate more strongly narrowed caudally, with long stout setae on distal half. Connective with arms shorter than stem. Style with preapical lobe well developed, apical apophysis short, thumblike, slightly curved laterally, with pointed apex. Aedeagus with well developed dorsal apodeme, preatrium short, shaft compressed, curved caudo-dorsally with three to four rows of spicules on lateral margin ventrally, apex with U-shaped excavation; gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,573,2005]" box="[199,737,933,958]" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">
<emphasis box="[199,284,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="10">Length.</emphasis>
